                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(center)\">\n                <placeName>Office of the</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"align(center)\"><placeName>JEWISH RECORD</placeName>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"align(center)\">\n                <placeName>No. 102 NASSAU STREET, N. Y.</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <date>October 28<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 1862</date>\n            </p>\n            <p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Dear Sir.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Your letter, was<lb/> handed to us a day or two ago by<lb/>\n                <persName>Mr. M. S. Isaacs</persName>. In answer we<lb/> would say that it will ever\n                be<lb/> our desire to keep the good will<lb/> of all men, but when attacked we<lb/>\n                must necessarily defend ourselves.<lb/> In our reply to your article which<lb/> to\n                say the least if not so intended<lb/> was calculated to dampen the prospects<lb/> of\n                young beginners we have said<lb/> nothing which on mature re-<lb/>flection we intend\n                to take back.<lb/> Respecting insinuations on your moral<lb/> character we are at a\n                loss to understand<lb/> your meaning we have not as far as<lb/> we can see mentioned\n                your private</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p37941d8f/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
